Cape Town – Police discovered a cache of explosives, ammunition and ivory in Francis Albert Street in Durbanville at the weekend. Members of the Bomb Disposal Unit were called to a scene in Durbanville where they made the discovery, police said. “Members of Cape Town K9 unit responded to a request for assistance in Francis Albert Street, Durbanville. According to the members, the son of a man who died in the month of April this year asked them to accompany him to his father's house. "There the members opened a firearm safe in the garage and found licensed firearms (two hunting rifles, one shotgun and one revolver),” said the police. The deceased previously worked for Denel and the State Information Technology Agency (Sita). “The members also found ammunition, two elephant tusks and a stack of explosives. The circumstances of the discovery are now under investigation,” said the police. Cape Times